author: The Current
description:
Mt. Joy keyboardist Jackie Miclau got to throw a first pitch at a Cubs game
Support The Current: https://support.mpr.org/youtube or hit the Thanks button

Mt. Joy keyboard player Jackie Miclau recently got to throw out a ceremonial first pitch at a Chicago Cubs home game. Miclau and her bandmates shared the story in an interview with The Current’s Zach McCormick.

When Mt. Joy were in Chicago for a concert at United Center on September 13, they visited Wrigley Field earlier in the day as the Chicago Cubs took on the Tampa Bay Rays. Miclau threw one of the ceremonial first pitches before the game; also honored that day was longtime Cubs first baseman Anthony Rizzo, who celebrated his retirement at Wrigley with a ceremonial first pitch of his own. Another musician in attendance for the festivities was Eddie Vedder of Pearl Jam.
